vague or thin pages rarely make the cut.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How do I show up in Google AI Overviews and AI Mode?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Follow Google's site-owner guidance for AI features: create content that's helpful and reliable, structured with clear headings that answer questions directly, and deep enough that users get real value on click-through. FAQ and HowTo schema can help Google extract structured answers from your page.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Does Perplexity respect robots.txt?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Perplexity states PerplexityBot respects robots.txt for indexing full and partial text content, but may still index a domain, headline, and brief factual summary even if blocked. For AEO, allow public citation pages to be crawled. For private content, use authentication rather than relying on robots.txt alone.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How should I structure a site for Australia + Spain (English + Spanish)?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Use distinct URL structures for each locale (subfolders like /au/ and /es/) and implement hreflang annotations so systems serve and cite the correct language version. Treat each locale's content as a separate editorial project — AU pages built for Australian readers, ES pages built for Spanish readers.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Is translating Australian content into Spanish enough for AEO?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"No. Translation without localisation creates mismatched examples, unnatural phrasing, and weak trust signals. Spain pages need Spain-relevant terminology, Spain regulatory context, and Spain examples. A page that feels translated is less likely to be cited by AI systems evaluating contextual relevance.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"What's the biggest AEO mistake for Australia + Spain setups?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Blocking AI crawlers without realising it. Many sites added aggressive bot-blocking rules in 2024–2025 to stop AI training scrapers but inadvertently blocked search crawlers (OAI-SearchBot, PerplexityBot) that drive citation visibility. Check your robots.txt and WAF configuration before anything else.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"HowTo\",\n      \"name\": \"How to set up AEO for Australia + Spain\",\n      \"description\": \"Step-by-step guide to implementing AEO across a multilingual site targeting Australia and Spain.\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Person\",\n        \"name\": \"Mitch Chadban\"\n      },\n      \"step\": [\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Audit your bot access\",\n          \"text\": \"Check robots.txt and WAF rules to confirm OAI-SearchBot and PerplexityBot can access the pages you want cited. Many sites accidentally block these crawlers.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Set up your international URL structure\",\n          \"text\": \"Choose subfolders (/au/ and /es/) or subdomains (au. and es.) and implement hreflang for en-au, es-es, and x-default on every page that has a locale equivalent.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Localise — don't just translate\",\n          \"text\": \"Rewrite Spain pages for Spanish readers with Spain-specific terminology, examples, and regulatory context. Do the same for AU pages. Never copy-paste between locales.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Structure content for AI extraction\",\n          \"text\": \"Add a 40-60 word definition block near the top of each page. Use comparison tables, step lists, and standalone FAQ sections. Each section should be extractable without surrounding context.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Implement schema markup\",\n          \"text\": \"Add Article, FAQPage, and HowTo schema to relevant pages. Use Speakable schema on your most citable sections.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"HowToStep\",\n          \"name\": \"Track and audit quarterly\",\n          \"text\": \"Monitor conversational query growth in Search Console, brand query lift, AI referral traffic in GA4, and conversion performance on citation pages. Run a citation readiness audit every quarter.\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"SpeakableSpecification\",\n      \"cssSelector\": [\".definition-block\", \"#spain h3\", \"#spain p\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script> -->";
